    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-04T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-04T02:00:00-05:00" n="240"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d240">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1972: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-04T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 4, 1937—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 4—8:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>370. My 369, August 4, 2 p.m.<note n="39" xml:id="d240fn39">Not printed.</note>
                    Following sent Tientsin and repeated to Peiping and Hankow: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“August 4, 2 p.m. Your August 3, 3 p.m.<note n="40" xml:id="d240fn40">
                                <ref target="frus1937v03#pg_316">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>,
                                    p. 316</ref>.</note> and August 3, 4 p.m.,<note n="39"
                                xml:id="d240fn1">Not printed.</note> are being repeated to Hankow.
                            Please furnish list of Americans and places of residence contained in
                            your August 3, 4 p.m., and any others in your district concerning whose
                            safety you may be in doubt to Japanese Consul General for information of
                            Japanese military and with request that military take note thereof with
                            a view to the protection of their lives and property in places where
                            Japanese may be active.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
